He then ran to the line of fire and, with the "greatest courage", moved the line forward before reaching a cannon with one hand and knocking down three of the detachment.
Lieutenant Colonel Vann was killed by a German sniper on 4 October 1918, only a month after the war ended.
Michael Vann, 72, said his grandfather's actions were "so great that I will never be able to live up to him, but they were very instructive."
