It was the first time the Navy had returned a ship to a shipyard after it had been delivered.
Little was known of the reasons behind the return, but German media cited a number of crucial "software and hardware defects" that left the ship virtually useless if sent to a combat mission.
Weaknesses in software were particularly important, as Baden-Wuerttemberg-class ships will be operated by a crew of about 120 sailors: half the personnel in the former Bremen-class frigates.
It was also found that the ship is overweight, which reduces its performance and limits the Navy's ability to add future updates.
