The two counts carry a possible death penalty, according to the court document.
Several weeks after the attack, a federal grand jury filed a 22-charge indictment with Saipov that included eight counts of murder with the aid of organized crime, which federal prosecutors usually use in these cases, and a charge of violence and destruction of motorized vehicles.
The attack required "substantial planning and premeditation," according to prosecutors, who described how Saipov carried it out as "atrocious, cruel, and depraved."
"Sayfullo Habibullaevic Saipov caused injuries, damages and losses to the families and friends of Diego Enrique Angelini, Nicholas Cleves, Ann-Laure Decadt, Darren Drake, Ariel Erlij, Hernan Ferruchi, Hernan Diego Mendoza and Alejandro Damian Pagnucco", is specified in the intent notice.
